\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Will add mod wheel events over time, increasing vibrato on long-held notes. Not all voices do that, so adds a little character to dull tones... This particular script works on all selected takes/tracks. Not required to be working within the MIDI Editor, but your MIDI notes need to be selected.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 \fmodern Courier;}}
